--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Usage
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 perl test-harness.plx -f FILENAME	run test harness with FILENAME config file

 perl test-harness.plx -nf FILENAME	run test harness with given test harness 
                                    config file, but don't run tests (for cross-
                                    compiling machines)

 perl test-harness.plx -tf FILENAME	run test harness with given test harness-
                                    config file, but don't configure and build--
                                    only run tests (for cross-compiling 
                                    machines)

 perl test-harness.plx -p FILENAME	parse FILENAME config file and exit--this is 
                                    useful for catching errors and 
                                    inconsistencies without running the entire 
                                    test-harness

 perl test-harness.plx -g FILENAME	generate commented config file (with 
									defaults) named FILENAME and exit

 perl test-harness.plx -sg FILENAME	generate uncommented config file (with 
									defaults) named FILENAME and exit

 perl test-harness.plx -h			print test harness help/usage information
									and exit

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Required Shell Programs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 mv, rm, cp, mkdir, find, date, uname, configure, make

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Directory Contents
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 test-harness.plx	    - test harness perl executable
 dependencies  			- list of all Trilinos package dependencies
 README					- this README file

 config/				- test harness config files
 elements-machine/		- machine-dependent invoke-configure elements
 elements-trilinos/		- machine-independent invoke-configure elements

 lib/                   - location of perl modules required by the test harness

 results/               - location of output if REPORT_METHOD is 
                          LOCAL_FILESYSTEM

 test-harness           - old test harness (deprecated)
 checkin-test-harness   - old checkin test harness (deprecated)
 subdir-list            - old test harness data file (deprecated)
